title: For Sale:  308 168 gr Moly Coated Black Hills Ammunition 168gr .308 match
location: Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: I have 7 boxes remaining of factory new / older stock Black Hills 168 grain HPBT Moly-Coated Match ammo. That's 138 rounds total, 20 rounds per box (one box has 18), 7 boxes. Moly coated bullets tend to reduce copper build-up in barrels, and the coating reduces friction and pressure as the bullet travels down the barrel, thus slowing down heat build-up, and allowing you to shoot for longer periods of time before groups start to wander from hot-barrel effects. These have been said to shoot remarkably well (consistently 1/2 moa or less) I've switched to 175 gr, so I have no use for these anymore, but the ammo is excellent, and no longer easily found. It may have been too expensive for Black Hills to continue producing these bullets, and I think they stopped making them . So here's a chance to pick-up some stock.

title: For Sale:  1943 M44 Mosin Nagant Carbine - Combat Trial Rifle - RARE
postcontent: Up for sale is a very rare Mosin Nagant. It's a Model 1944 Mosin Nagant Carbine, but it's a trial rifle made in 1943 using an M38. Only around 50,000 trial rifles were built in 1943, compared to the 7 million+ produced from 1944-1948. These trial rifles were made to test in combat and it definitely saw use. It has some very interesting stock repairs unlike any I've ever seen vefore on a Mosin. The parts are force matched with electro pencil. All done during refurbishment. If you're familiar with Mosins, you know what I'm talking about. The rifle is in extremely good shape and the bore is very nice. Rifle is from the Izvhesk weapons factory and shoots 7.62x54R. Also has a pretty nice trigger for a Mosin. Rifle operates flawlessly and makes huge fire balls from the muzzel. This rifle is an extremely cool conversation piece.I have tons of pictures of it, so if you're interested, shoot me a text and I can send them.
